               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18381022-name-989" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18381022-name-989" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381022-name-989" type="surname" value="MILLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18381022-name-989" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES MILLER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a private in the Royal Veterans. I was in Royal Hospital-row, Chelsea, on the 12th of October, looking for a lodging—the prisoner came up, and said, if I wanted an honest lodging, he would get me one—I went with him to the Cheshire Cheese—we went on to the College-walk, and a man came up with some apples—I wanted to buy some, and pulled out my purse—the prisoner snatched it from ray hand, and ran off—it contained a sovereign, four half-crowns, a shilling, and some halfpence.</p>
